class Solution {
public:
    void helper(int idx,vector<int>& nums,vector<int> ds,vector<vector<int>>& res)
    {
       //base case
       if(idx<0)
       {
          res.push_back(ds);
          return;
       }

       //not pick 
       helper(idx-1,nums,ds,res);

       //pick case
       ds.push_back(nums[idx]);
       helper(idx-1,nums,ds,res);
    }
    vector<vector<int>> subsets(vector<int>& nums) 
    {
        vector<vector<int>> res;
        vector<int> ds;

        helper(nums.size()-1,nums,ds,res);
        return res;
    }
};

Time Complexity: O(n × 2ⁿ)

- Each element has 2 choices (Pick / Not Pick).
- Total subsets generated = 2ⁿ.
- Copying each subset into the result takes O(n).
- Therefore, total time = O(n × 2ⁿ).

Space Complexity:

Auxiliary Space: O(n)
- Maximum recursion depth is n.

Including Output: O(n × 2ⁿ)
- There are 2ⁿ subsets, each can contain up to n elements.
